chart.name: Mean time (ms) per request, across hosts
4XX and 5XX responses per sec
chart.programText:
A = data('http.server.requests.count', filter=filter('status', '4*')).mean(by=['status', 'uri']).publish(label='A')
B = data('http.server.requests.count', filter=filter('status', '5*')).mean(by=['status', 'uri']).publish(label='B')

chart.name: Mean/Max time (ms) per request, by status
Top time (ms) per request, by host
Total HTTP client requests by status
Mean time (ms) per request, by status
chart.programText:
A = data('http.server.requests.totalTime').mean(by=['status']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
G = data('http.server.requests.count', rollup='sum').sum(by=['status']).publish(label='G', enable=False)
H = (A/G).scale(1000).publish(label='H')
